 ONE person was reportedly killed on Monday in a clash between two factional groups of Odua Peoples Congress in Ikoyi community in Isokan Local Government Area, Osun State. It was gathered that the clash followed a heated argument between Nurudeen Emiola who is a member of Odua Peoples Congress Initiative, and Abiodun Ogunjimi, of Odua Peoples Congress. Police spokesperson Mrs Yemisi Opalola confirmed the incident, saying, “One person called Bolaji Owolewa was killed and his body deposited in a morgue.” Three other persons were inhured, she said. 